	<h1>Irene Iodice</h1>

		<img src="{{ base }}/images/bio.jpeg" align="left"  width="33%" height="36%" style="margin: 0px 30px 10px 0px;"/> <p>

	<p>I am an applied economist specialising in international trade and political economy. I am Assistant Professor of Economics at Bielefeld University and a CESifo Research Network Affiliate. I hold a PhD in Economics (joint) from the Sant’Anna School of Advanced Studies and Université Paris 1 Panthéon–Sorbonne. Before joining Bielefeld, I was a postdoctoral researcher with Maria Bas (ANR MoQuAT) and a consultant to the World Bank.</p>

	  <div style="clear:both; margin-top:0.75rem;"></div>

	
		<p>My current research focuses on the following areas:</p>
<ul style="margin-top: 0; margin-bottom: 0;">
    <li><p style="margin: 0;">Trade Agreements and Regional Supply Chains</p></li>
    <li><p style="margin: 0;">Non-tariff measures and their impact on firms' production networks and exports</p></li>
    <li><p style="margin: 0;">Trade Elasticity and Firm Dynamics</p></li>
    <li><p style="margin: 0;">Globalization and Labor Market Dynamics</p></li>
</ul>

	<p> You can contact me at firstname.lastname@uni-bielefeld.de <p> 

